<paragraph id="354B36B45677FFC2D3F7F9EFFC7E63B5" blockId="107.[684,1212,1251,1738]" pageId="107" pageNumber="107">
UNVOUCHERED OBSERVATIONS: One individual of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375677FFC2D3CFF9CFFB93633A" baseAuthorityName="Rouk &amp; D.C.Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[756,1060,1581,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65677FFC2D3CFF9CFFB93633A" box="[756,1060,1581,1605]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="107">Platyrrhinus brachycephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was captured at Tapiche during the Sierra del Divisor Rapid Biological Inventory (Jorge and Velazco, 2006), and we captured one individual at El Chino Village on 
<date id="414A10745677FFC2D239F950FC7263B5" box="[770,965,1714,1738]" pageId="107" pageNumber="107" value="2019-02-16">16 February 2019</date>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45670FFC5D1B7FF00FF0C668D" blockId="108.[108,637,226,1539]" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">
IDENTIFICATION: 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375670FFC5D076FF00FDCB6585" baseAuthorityName="Rouk &amp; D.C.Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[333,636,226,250]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65670FFC5D076FF00FDCB6585" box="[333,636,226,250]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Platyrrhinus brachycephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widely distributed Amazonian species that also occurs in the montane forests of eastern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D157FEA7FF7F6422" box="[108,200,325,349]" name="Ecuador" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and eastern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D069FEA7FE326423" box="[338,389,325,348]" name="Peru" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Peru</collectingCountry>
(Velazco, 2005). It can be distinguished from other congeneric species by the following characteristics: small size (forearm &lt;
<quantity id="F20C9B515670FFC5D197FE4AFF4A64BF" box="[172,253,424,448]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="108" pageNumber="108" unit="mm" value="42.0">42 mm</quantity>
), U-shaped notch in posterior margin of uropatagium, outline of lateral margin of pterygoid process narrowly concave (small and c-shaped) in posterior view, and anterolingual cristid of the second lower premolar bearing two well-developed accessory cuspulids (Velazco, 2005; Velazco et al., 2010a; López-Baucells et al., 2018). Descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375670FFC5D351FD72FEA367B6" baseAuthorityName="Rouk &amp; D.C.Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65670FFC5D351FD72FEA367B6" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">P. brachycephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were provided by Rouk and Carter (1972), Swanepoel and Genoways (1979), Williams and Genoways (1980a), Brosset and Charles-Dominique (1990), Velazco (2005), Velazco et al. (2010a), and Velazco and Lim (2014). Two subspecies are currently recognized: 
<emphasis id="0780EAA65670FFC5D157FC9AFEF066F0" box="[108,327,887,911]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">
P. b. 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375670FFC5D19FFC95FEF066F0" baseAuthorityName="Rouk &amp; D.C.Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[164,327,887,911]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">brachycephalus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D062FC95FE7D66F0" box="[345,458,887,911]" name="Colombia" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D0E3FC95FD8266F0" box="[472,565,887,911]" name="Ecuador" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D378FC9AFDCF66F0" box="[579,632,888,911]" name="Peru" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D157FC7AFF1966CF" box="[108,174,920,944]" name="Brazil" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D1D5FC7AFE8A66CF" box="[238,317,920,944]" name="Bolivia" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<emphasis id="0780EAA65670FFC5D0BAFC7BFD9666CF" box="[385,545,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">P. b. saccharus</emphasis>
(northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE376245670FFC5D1FDFC5BFE8166AE" box="[198,310,953,977]" name="Venezuela" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and the Guianas) (Gardner, 2008f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45670FFC5D1B7FC19FF526042" blockId="108.[108,637,226,1539]" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">
Ascorra et al. (1993) and Medina et al. (2015) correctly identified their material from Jenaro 
<collectingRegion id="F730F8565670FFC5D157FBDCFF73612A" box="[108,196,1086,1109]" country="Panama" name="Herrera" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Herrera</collectingRegion>
, Quebrada Betilia, Quebrada Lobo, and Quebrada Pantaleón as 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375670FFC5D04BFBBCFF2F61E8" baseAuthorityName="Rouk &amp; D.C.Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65670FFC5D04BFBBCFF2F61E8" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Platyrrhinus brachycephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The voucher material we examined from the Yavarí-Ucayali interfluve conforms to previous descriptions of 
<emphasis id="0780EAA65670FFC5D06EFB20FD8061A5" box="[341,567,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">
P. b. 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375670FFC5D0A9FB20FD8061A5" baseAuthorityName="Rouk &amp; D.C.Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[402,567,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">brachycephalus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, with measurements that fall within the range of size variation previously documented for the subspecies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45670FFC5D1B7FAA4FDDB637C" blockId="108.[108,637,226,1539]" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">
REMARKS: All three recorded captures of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375670FFC5D373FAA4FECD6000" baseAuthorityName="Rouk &amp; D.C.Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="108" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65670FFC5D373FAA4FECD6000" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="108">Platyrrhinus brachycephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accompanied by ecological information from our region were in mistnets: one in an elevated net in a clearing, another in a ground-level net in a clearing, and a third in a ground-level net in primary forest.
</paragraph>
